# Normalize line endings. Without this, editors on Windows silently rewrite files
# to CRLF, producing whole-file "phantom" diffs that bury the real change (this
# happened: a 6-line .gitignore edit showed up as 344 changed lines).
# text=auto lets git detect text files and store them with LF in the repo;
# eol=lf checks them out as LF everywhere.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Belt and braces: never run EOL conversion on the binary artifacts we ship.
# text=auto already auto-detects these, but marking them explicitly means a
# mis-detection can never corrupt a model, capture, or image.
*.pcap   binary
*.pcapng binary
*.joblib binary
*.keras  binary
*.h5     binary
*.png    binary
*.parquet binary
